  <source>University Hospital, Antwerp</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The current study is a dubble-blinde placebo-controlled cross-over study verifying the
      preventive effect of antioxidants on noise-induced hearing loss (NIHL) and noise-induced
      tinnitus (NIT). The antioxidants comprise of a mixture of magnesium and n-acetylcystein which
      should be taken 1h before leisure noise above 100dB for at least 30 minutes.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
